‘—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2019-11-01-twin0010.mdЩ@1df438da0988196438b81dd849611f98667f41bf0827980b9b9ead31bc5783bdіThis week in Nu #10‘іThis week in Nu #10Ъ4Lots of new commands this week, some updates in how we handle paths and column paths, better debugging capabilities, improved command help, more work towards getting Nu ready to be a login shell, and more documentation.
We're currently running a 
[link: https://t.co/nujSjnI0dr?amp=1] short survey about Nu
. Even if you aren't a Nu user, we'd love to hear from you!
wycats added better tracing for debugging the parser (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/892] #892
)
notryanb updated 
``fetch``
 to be able to load URLs from strings and $it (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/886] #886
)
jonathandturner added updates to always save history (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/881] #881
); added parameter descriptions to command help (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/882] #882
); added new builtin variables 
``$nu:config``
, 
``$nu:env``
, and 
``$nu:path``
(
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/883] #883
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/884] #884
); added support for reading the PATH from config (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/885] #885
), added a new 
``read``
 command for easier text handling (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/889] #889
), and added 
``prepend``
 and 
``append``
 for adding rows to tables (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/890] #890
)
andrasio added more support for working with ~ in paths across platforms (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/879] #879
) as well as added initial support for row numbers in column paths (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/892] #892
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/898] #898
)
andrasio also worked on better separation between the parser and other subsystems (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/874] #874
)
oknozor and loksonarius added more documentation for commands (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/871] #871
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/873] #873
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/899] #899
)
’ђђЪrTitle: This week in Nu #10
Path: This week in Nu #10
Content:
Lots of new commands this week, some updates in how we handle paths and column paths, better debugging capabilities, improved command help, more work towards getting Nu ready to be a login shell, and more documentation.
We're currently running a 
[link: https://t.co/nujSjnI0dr?amp=1] short survey about Nu
. Even if you aren't a Nu user, we'd love to hear from you!
wycats added better tracing for debugging the parser (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/892] #892
)
notryanb updated 
``fetch``
 to be able to load URLs from strings and $it (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/886] #886
)
jonathandturner added updates to always save history (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/881] #881
); added parameter descriptions to command help (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/882] #882
); added new builtin variables 
``$nu:config``
, 
``$nu:env``
, and 
``$nu:path``
(
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/883] #883
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/884] #884
); added support for reading the PATH from config (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/885] #885
), added a new 
``read``
 command for easier text handling (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/889] #889
), and added 
``prepend``
 and 
``append``
 for adding rows to tables (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/890] #890
)
andrasio added more support for working with ~ in paths across platforms (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/879] #879
) as well as added initial support for row numbers in column paths (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/892] #892
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/898] #898
)
andrasio also worked on better separation between the parser and other subsystems (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/874] #874
)
oknozor and loksonarius added more documentation for commands (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/871] #871
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/873] #873
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/899] #899
)
